article.headline: Iona 70, Canisius 66
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Ricky Soliver made a tie-breaking jumper with 5.8 seconds left and Marvin McCullough sealed the win with a steal and two free throws with 1.1 seconds left as Iona beat Canisius 70-66 Friday night. After Canisius turned the ball over with 38 seconds left and the game tied at 66-all, Soliver hit a jumper from just inside the free throw line to put Iona (7-12, 5-5 MAAC) up for good. After a timeout, McCullough intercepted a pass by Jon Ferris then hit the free throws that clinched the victory. McCullough led Iona (7-12, 5-5) with 12 points. DeShaun Williams had 11, while Greg Jenkins and Tariq Atkins each finished with 10. Canisius (7-13, 2-7) grabbed a game-high nine-point lead, 50-41, on Yaku Moton-Spruill's layup with 13:16 left. However, the Gaels scored the next eight points, six of them by Atkins. Canisius still held the lead until a steal and jumper by McCullough tied the game 66-66 with 45 seconds left. Toby Foster finished with 11 points and 10 rebounds for the Golden Griffins, who committed 19 turnovers. Dewitt Doss added 10 points. The victory was Iona's seventh straight over Canisius.
